The paper deals with dimension reduction, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in various fields. The use of hashing and local densification suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT) categories. The focus on sparsity and compressed sensing also suggests a possible fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) categories. Finally, the use of streaming algorithms and approximation techniques suggests a possible fit with the signal processing (cs.SI) category.
